>> Could you donate your time to raise awareness of diabetes?
>> We need your help make a difference to the lives of hundreds of thousands
of people in London living with diabetes. Diabetes UK London offers
>> **Please note that due to government guidance on social distancing we are
currently not recruiting any new volunteers for any of the roles below. We
will keep this page and updated and will let you know when we are able to
>> We have a variety of volunteer roles to suit many interests and a variety
>> * Know your risk volunteers talk to members of the public and to
those at risk of diabetes, encouraging them to undergo a risk assessment using
the diabetes risk score system. For more information have a look at the Know
>> * Raise awareness of diabetes as an event volunteer through helping
out at our roadshows and other health awareness events.
>> * Participate in the Speaker Scheme by delivering awareness talks and
>> * Become a Community Champion and raise awareness of diabetes and
promote healthy lifestyles to people in diverse communities.
>> * Join one of our local groups or start your own. Most meet monthly
and give individuals the opportunity to get support for their diabetes,
fundraise, hear talks from external speakers and much more.
>> * Campaign through Diabetes Voices or promote your personal story
>> * Give your time as an office volunteer and be involved in organising
events, providing admin support, researching and gathering information.
>> * Attend training and networking events to develop your skills for
your volunteer role and meet like-minded and passionate volunteers.
>> If you would like to make a difference, get involved, receive further
details or have any questions then please contact us to find out more.
>> Get in touch if you'd like to volunteer
